    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>The Goblin Monarch is a self-styled ruler wearing a crown of bent nails and copper wire. It leads its tribe not by strength but by sheer force of personality and pragmatism -- it would rather negotiate than lose soldiers, but it fights with real cunning when pushed.</p><p>These goblins have been driven from deep mountain caves by something pressing southwest. The Monarch doesn't know what it is. It's as frightened as it is dangerous.</p>",
      "director": "<p>The Monarch fights from range on the boulder, throwing axes at two targets per turn while letting Runners and Warriors absorb damage. Get in Here! replenishes minion bodies. Meat Shield keeps the Monarch alive when targeted by name. When the Runners pile up, Kill! punishes clusters.</p><p>Negotiation is possible (hard Presence test or shared food). The Monarch is pragmatic -- it wants its people alive more than it wants a fight. If PCs attempt to parley before initiative, consider offering a skill test rather than combat.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
